sit up like Jacky
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to sit up straight, with confidence; to be on good behaviour.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:-
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1935 Havelock
Citations
Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGill
Vol / Page: 102
Edition:
Quote: sit up like Jacky to behave at one's best, or confidently; Jacky being a common name for many people and things; the origins are uncertain, but the common name for an organ grinder's monkey is likely; c. 1930. NZA.
